sinessfocused organization with four divisions enterprise group which works in servers storage networking consulting and support services software and financial services the split was structured so that the old hewlettpackard changed its name to hp inc and spun off hewlett packard enterprise as a newly created company hp inc which retained the old hps personal computer and printing business retained the old hps stockprice history and the original nyse ticker symbol for hewlettpackard while enterprise trades under its own ticker symbol hpe according to notes from which hpes revenue was slightly less than that of hp inc in  it spun off its enterprise services business to become dxc technology contents  naming  history  executive leadership  products  see also  references  external links namingedit the full name for the company is hewlett packard enterprise company which drops the hyphen that previously existed between the hewlett and packard of the former hewlettpackard company during and since the separation many media outlets have incorrectly named the new organization with some using hp enterprises or hp enterprise historyedit in may  the company announced it would sell its enterprise services division to one of its competitors computer sciences corporation in a deal valued at  billion the merger of hpe enterprise services with csc to form a new company dxc technology was completed on  march  approximately  current hpe employees are affected more than  services employees from other areas of the hpe business will remain at hpe including technology services support and consulting as well as software professional services in august  the company announced plans to acquire silicon graphics international sgi known for their capabilities in high performance computing on november   hpe announced it completed the acquisition for  per share in cash a transaction valued at approximately  million net of cash and debt on september   hpe announced a spinmerge with micro focus where micro focus would acquire its noncore software and hpe shareholders would own  percent of the merged company which would retain its current name in november  pc world wrote “hpe and before it hewlettpackard failed to develop middleware tools to really make a dent in the software market where other companies like ibm sap and oracle are excelling” and that without major software product lines hpe’s integrated offerings won’t be as strong as competitors like dell which have the software and hardware assets adding that “if all hpe is doing at this point is focusing largely on hardware you have to ask what the end game here is” in september  hewlett packard enterprise has transferred two patents to a texas based wholly owned shell company plectrum llc these two patents were originated at the com corporation which was bought by hp in  along with about  patents us patent no  is entitled quality of service control mechanism and apparatus while us patent no  describes the use of a high speed cache management unit which replaces some softwarebased systems with hardware in order to reduce latency timecitation needed on april   it was reported that synack had raised  million in a round of funding that included hewlett packard enterprise in april  hewlett packard enterprise completed its acquisition of hybrid flash and all flash manufacturer nimble storage inc for  billion or  per share executive leadershipedit meg whitman  chief executive officer antonio neri  president and general manager enterprise group henry gomez  executive vice president chief marketing and communications officer tim stonesifer  executive vice president chief financial officer john schultz  executive vice president general counsel and corporate secretary alan may  executive vice president human resources productsedit hpe servers proliant hpe integrity servers nonstop hpe superdome apollo for highperformance computingl hpe networking procurve com aruba networks hpe storage hpe par hp storageworks hp xp hpe software hp openview hp cloud service automation software hp business service automation hp service manager software and hpe records manager software etc see alsoedit hp inc – the demerged sibling company that offers printers and personal computers hewlett packard enterprise services – former global business unit of hewlett packard enterprise that provides managed and outsourced services hewlett packard labs – the research  development arm of hpe hewlett packard enterprise software – a global business unit of hewlett packard enterprise that sells big data analysis and security solutions referencesedit  hp to cut up to  jobs  al jazeera america   larry dignan hp inc hpe launch questions abound for both zdnet   hewlettpackard becomes hp inc and hewlett packard enterprise   bailey brandon  may  hp enterprise selling tech services business to rival st louis postdispatch retrieved  may  permanent dead link  hewlett packard enterprise wins “gold” in data analytics highperformance computing with acquisition of sgi wwwhpecom retrieved    httpswwwhpecomusennewsroomnewsarchivepressreleasehewlettpackardenterprisecompletesacquisitionofsgihtml  httpinvestorssgicomreleasedetailcfmreleaseid  christine wang  hewlett packard enterprise earnings  cents per share vs  cents eps est cnbc retrieved    a year after separation hp and hp enterprise are still trying to shed rust pc worl retrieved  november    kuchler hannah april   hackerforhire company synack raises m financial times retrieved april    external linksedit official website business data for hewlett packard enterprise google finance yahoo finance reuters sec filings v t e hewlettpackard hp inc hewlett packard enterprise dxc technology micro focus founders william hewlett david packard directors marc andreessen shumeet banerji raj gupta raymond j lane ann livermore gary m reiner patricia f russo jim skinner meg whitman chairman executive officers meg whitman todd bradley dave donatelli martin fink henry gomez john hinshaw 