wlettpackard company hpe is a businessfocused organization with four divisions enterprise group which works in servers storage networking consulting and support services software and financial services the split was structured so that the old hewlettpackard changed its name to hp inc and spun off hewlett packard enterprise as a newly created company hp inc which retained the old hps personal computer and printing business retained the old hps stockprice history and the original nyse ticker symbol for hewlettpackard while enterprise trades under its own ticker symbol hpe according to notes from which hpes revenue was slightly less than that of hp inc in  it spun off its enterprise services business to become dxc technology contents  naming  history  executive leadership  products  see also  references  external links namingedit the full name for the company is hewlett packard enterprise company which drops the hyphen that previously existed between the hewlett and packard of the former hewlettpackard company during and since the separation many media outlets have incorrectly named the new organization with some using hp enterprises or hp enterprise historyedit in may  the company announced it would sell its enterprise services division to one of its competitors computer sciences corporation in a deal valued at  billion the merger of hpe enterprise services with csc to form a new company dxc technology was completed on  march  approximately  current hpe employees are affected more than  services employees from other areas of the hpe business will remain at hpe including technology services support and consulting as well as software professional services in august  the company announced plans to acquire silicon graphics international sgi known for their capabilities in high performance computing on november   hpe announced it completed the acquisition for  per share in cash a transaction valued at approximately  million net of cash and debt on september   hpe announced