 a b c why hewlettpackards impulse buy didnt pay off bloomberg businessweek november   apotheker believed that hps platform was sinkingand appeared to be in a hurry to transform the company in a rapid series of moves announced in august  apotheker killed hps sixweekold touchpad tablet explored plans for a spinout of its pc business and championed the  billion acquisition of autonomy one former hp executive who worked there at the time says it appeared that apotheker and the board didnt know what to do and were trying anything they could think of it wasnt a strategy he says it was chaos oracle ceo larry ellison called autonomys asking price absurdly high  hpq stock since naming leo apotheker ceo   a b c autonomy board backs £bn hewlettpackard offer the daily telegraph august    a b hp closes autonomy deal reuters november   hewlettpackard completed its  billion buy of british software firm autonomy on monday the centerpiece of a botched strategy shift that cost exchief executive leo apotheker his job last month hp said its  poundspershare cash offer – representing a  percent premium that many hp shareholders found excessive – had been accepted by investors  a b c d e f rage of the titans whitman vs lynch the daily telegraph november    a b c d e f motion by hussain  p  hp names meg whitman as ceo   new hewlettpackard chief meg whitman gets  salary leo apotheker gets m the australian september    hp to keep pc division october     brandon bailey march   hp to combine pc printing units san jose mercury news retrieved march     poornima gupta may   analysts back hewlettpackards layoff plans reuters retrieved may     httptimesofindiaindiatimescomtechcareersjobtrendshpannouncesjobcutsarticleshowcms the times of india  external link in title help missing or empty url help accessdate requires url help  pcmaker hp unveils its first netzero energy data centre the times of india may     zeroday vulnerability found in the server monitoring software of hp retrieved july     hp s