ally well for its disclosure of externally verified greenhouse gas emissions and its setting of targets for reducing themthirdparty source needed however greenpeace reports that hp risks a penalty point in future editions due to the fact that it is a member of trade associations that have commented against energy efficiency standards hp has earned recognition of its work in the area of data privacy and security in  the company ranked no  in the ponemon institutes annual study of the most trusted companies for privacy since  hp has worked directly with the us congress the federal trade commission ftc and the department of commerce to establish a new strategy for federal legislation hp played a key role in work toward the december  ftc report protecting consumer privacy in an era of rapid change after winning nine straight annual most respected company in china awards from the economic observer and peking university hp china has added the  year contribution award to its list of accolades the award aims to identify companies doing business in china with outstanding and sustained performance in business operations development and corporate social responsibility in its  rankings of consumer electronics companies on progress relating to conflict minerals the enough project rated hp second out of  companies calling it a pioneer of progress brandedit a hewlettpackard sponsored porsche  gt cup the company sponsored the hp pavilion at san jose now sap center at san jose home to the nhls san jose sharks according to a businessweek study hp was the worlds th most valuable brand as of  hp has many sponsorships one well known sponsorship is mission space in epcot at the walt disney world resort from  to  and again from  hp has been the shirt sponsor of premier league club tottenham hotspur fccitation needed from  to  they were sponsors of australian football league club north melbourne football clubcitation needed they also sponsored the bmw williams formula  team until  a sponsorship formerly held by compaq and as of  sponsor renault f hewlettpackard also had the naming rights arrangement for the hp pavilion at san jose home of the san jose sharks nhl hockey team until  in which the arenas naming rights were acquired by sap ag renaming the arena to the sap center at san jose the company also maintains a number of corporate sponsorships in the business sector including sponsorships of trade organisations including fespa print trade exhibitions and oreilly medias velocity web development conference after the acquisition of compaq in  hp has maintained the compaq presario brand on lowend home desktops and laptops the hp compaq brand on business desktops and laptops and the hp proliant brand on intelarchitecture servers the hp pavilion brand is used on home entertainment laptops and all home desktops tandems nonstop servers are now branded as hp integrity nonstop hp discover customer eventedit in  hp enterprise business along with participating independent user groups combined its annual hp software universe hp technology forum and hp technologywork into a single event hp discover there are two hp discover events annually one for the americas and one for europe middle east and africa emea hp discover  americas took place june – in las vegas at the venetianpalazzo the company demonstrated the webos touchpad introduced july   the hp discover  event in emea took place in vienna austria on november  through december   controversiesedit restatementedit in march  hp restated its firstquarter cash flow from operations reducing it  percent because of an accounting error actual cash flow from operations was  million not  million as reported earlier hp shifted  million to net cash used in investing activities spying scandaledit main article hewlettpackard spying scandal on september   shawn cabalfin and david oneil of newsweek wrote that hps general counsel at the behest of chairwoman patricia dunn contracted a team of independent security experts to investigate board members and several journalists in order to identify the source of an information leak in turn those security experts recruited private investigators who used a spying technique known as pretexting the pretexting involved investigators impersonating hp board members and nine journalists including reporters for cnet the new york times and the wall street journal in order to obtain their phone records the information leaked related to hps longterm strategy and was published as part of a cnet article in january  most hp employees accused of criminal acts have since been acquitted hardwareedit in november  hewlettpackard released a bios update covering a wide range of laptops with the intent to speed up the computer fan as well as have it run constantly whether the computer was on or off the reason was to prevent the overheating of defective nvidia graphics processing units gpus that had been shipped to many of the original equipment manufacturers including hewlettpackard dell and apple the defect concerned the new packaging material used by nvidia from  onwards in joining the graphics chip onto the motherboard which did not perform well under thermal cycling and was prone to develop stress cracks – effectively severing the connection between the gpu and the motherboard leading to a blank screen in july  hp issued an extension to the initial oneyear warranty to replace the motherboards of selected models however this option was not extended to all models with the defective nvidia chipsets despite research showing that these computers were also affected by the fault furthermore the replacement of the motherboard was a temporary fix since the fault was inherent in all units of the affected models from the point of manufacture including the replacement motherboards offered by hp as a free repair since this point several websites have been documenting the issue most notably wwwhpliescom a forum dedicated to what they refer to as hewlettpackards multimillion dollar cover up of the issue and wwwnvidiadefectcom which details the specifics of the fault and offers advice to the owners of affected computers there have been several smallclaims lawsuits filed in several states as well as suits filed in other countries hewlettpackard also faced a classaction lawsuit in  over its i processor computers the complainants stated that their systems locked up within  minutes of powering on consistently even after being replaced with newer i systems the lockups continued lawsuit against oracleedit on june   hp filed a lawsuit in california superior court in santa clara claiming that oracle corporation had breached an agreement to support the itanium microprocessor used in hps highend enterprise servers on june   hp sent a formal legal demand letter to oracle in an attempt to force the worlds no  software maker to reverse its decision to discontinue software development on intel itanium microprocessor and build its own servers hp won the lawsuit in  requiring oracle to continue to produce software compatible with the itanium processor hp was awarded  billion in damages against oracle on june   hp argued oracles canceling support damaged hp itanium server brand oracle has announced it will appeal both the decision and damages takeover of autonomyedit see also autonomy corporation § hewlett packard in november  hp recorded a writedown of around  billion related to its acquisition a year earlier of the uk based autonomy corporation plc hp accused autonomy of deliberately inflating the value of the company prior to its takeover the former management team of autonomy flatly rejected the charge autonomy specialized in analysis of large scale unstructured big data and by  was the uks largest and most successful software business it maintained an aggressively entrepreneurial marketing approach and controls described as a rod of iron which was said to include zero tolerance and firing the weakest  of its sales force each quarter while compensating the best sales staff like rock stars at the time hp had fired its previous ceo for expenses irregularities a year before and appointed léo apotheker as ceo and president hp was seen as problematic by the market with margins falling and having failed to redirect and establish itself in major new markets such as cloud and mobile services apothekers strategy was to aim at disposing of hardware and moving into the more profitable software services sector as part of this strategy autonomy was acquired by hp in october  hp paid  billion for  of the shares valuing autonomy at around  billion £ billion overall a premium of around  over market price the deal was widely criticized as absurdly high a botched strategy shift and a chaotic attempt to rapidly reposition hp and enhance earnings and had been objected to even by hps own cfo– within a year apotheker himself had been fired major culture clashes became apparent and hp had written off  billion of autonomys value hp claim this resulted from accounting improprieties misrepresentations and disclosure failures by the previous management who in turn accuse hp of a textbook example of defensive stalling to conceal evidence of its own prior knowledge and gross mismanagement and undermining of the company noting public awareness since  of its financial reporting issues and that even hps cfo disagreed with the price paid– external observers generally state that only a small part of the writeoff appears to be due to accounting misstatements and that hp had overpaid for businesses previously the serious fraud office united kingdom and the us securities and exchange commission joined the fbi in investigating the potential anomalies hp incurred much damage with its stock falling to decades low three lawsuits were brought by shareholders against hp for the fall in value of hp shares in august  a united states district court judge threw out a proposed settlement which autonomys previous management had argued would be collusive and intended to divert scrutiny of hps own responsibility and knowledge by essentially engaging the plaintiffs attorneys from the existing cases and redirecting them against the previous autonomy vendors and management for a fee of up to  million with plaintiffs agreeing to end any claims against hps management and similarly redirect those claims against the previous autonomy vendors and management in january  the sfo closed its investigation as the likelihood of a successful prosecution was low the dispute is still being litigated in the us and is being investigated by the uk and ireland financial reporting council on june   hp agreed to pay  million to investors who bought hp shares between august   and november   to settle the suite over autonomy purchase israeli settlementsedit on october   richard falk the human rights council’s special rapporteur on the situation of human rights in the palestinian territories occupied since  called for boycotting hp together with other businesses that are profiting from israeli settlements on occupied palestinian lands until they brought their operations in line with international human rights and humanitarian law in  the presbyterian church voted to move forward with divestment from hp in protest of israeli policies toward palestinians in  the city of portlands human rights commission requested to place caterpillar gs hewlettpackard and motorola solutions on the city’s “do not buy” list briberyedit on april   an administrative proceeding before securities and exchange commission was settled by hp consenting to an order acknowledging that hp had violated the foreign corrupt practices act fcpa when hp subsidiaries in russia poland and mexico made improper payments to government officials to obtain or retain lucrative public contracts the secs order finds that hps subsidiary in russia paid more than  million through agents and various shell companies to a russian government official to retain a multimilliondollar contract with the federal prosecutors office in poland hps subsidiary provided gifts and cash bribes worth more than  to a polish government official to obtain contracts with the national police agency and as part of its bid to win a software sale to mexicos stateowned petroleum company hps subsidiary in mexico paid more than  million in inflated commissions to a consultant with close ties to company officials and money was funneled to one of those officials hp agreed to pay  million to settle the sec charges and a parallel criminal case see alsoedit san francisco bay area portal companies portal information technology portal arcsight fortify hp calculators hp linux imaging and printing hp software  solutions hp user group list of acquisitions by hewlettpackard list of computer system manufacturers list of hewlettpackard products shortest path bridging tippingpoint referencesedit  hp regains pc lead over lenovo pc pro january   retrieved april     lenovo shares jump as pc shipments overtake hp november    gartner says worldwide pc shipments grew  percent in fourth quarter of  gartner january   retrieved february     san jose mercury news hps acquisitions cement companys no  status chris obrien april  san jose mercury news retrieved november     hp completes acquisition of com corporation accelerates converged infrastructure strategy hewlettpackard retrieved july     vance ashlee wortham jenna april   hp to pay  billion for palm the new york times   dell gives up bidding war for par inc winstonsalem journal associated press september   archived from the original on january   retrieved september     hewlettpackard to split into two public companies october     hp retiree quotes and anecdotes about bill hewlett hpcom retrieved june     malone michael  bill  dave how hewlett and packard built the worlds greatest company portfolio hardcover pp – isbn    hp history hps garage hewlettpackard december   retrieved july     hp company information hp interactive timeline hewlettpackard retrieved 